# ============================================================
# Repo-wide ignore. Sub-projects (couple-buzz-server / couple-buzz-app)
# have their own .gitignore for project-specific paths (data/, dist/,
# certs/, etc). This file covers cross-cutting concerns + defense in
# depth so an accidental file never sneaks into a commit.
# ============================================================

# === macOS / Windows / Linux OS junk ===
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# === Editor / IDE ===
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
.claude/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# === Logs ===
*.log
logs/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# === Test / coverage ===
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# === Build output (sub-dirs already cover their own; this is a safety net) ===
dist/
build/
node_modules/

# === Secrets — env files, private keys, certs ===
# Sub-dir .gitignore already lists these for each app, but mirror them
# here so a file placed at the repo root can never leak.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p8
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.cer
*.crt
*.mobileprovision
secrets/

# === Backups / encrypted blobs ===
# Encrypted SQLite backups (.gpg) and exported GPG keys (.asc) must
# never be committed even if they're encrypted — they're operational
# data, not source.
*.gpg
*.asc
*.pgp
*.bak
*.backup
*.tar.gz
*.zip

# === Local-only scratchpad / private notes ===
# Convention: any file ending in .local or .private (or in a private/
# folder) is treated as never-committed. Useful for "I'll write down
# the VPS IP / SSH cmd / scratch ideas here" without risk.
*.local
*.local.*
*.private
*.private.*
private/
NOTES.md
TODO.private.md

# === Misc ===
.expo/
*.tsbuildinfo
